I solo in FG, trying to use as little mana as possible for best sustainable XP, dismissing pet before mob dies so I dont lose XP. I use Boots of Blade Calling to pull and throughout the fight. Earth pets are mostly immune to the fungi spells, and the shrooms wasting time casting prevents pet getting whacked so much (ideal situation for a mage).<br>
I use around 1/2 to 3/4 bub mana per kill. About every 7-8 shrooms I'd rod once and med/heal back up, say 7 minutes. Takes about 3-4 minutes prepare and kill each mob.<br>
<br>
Ok, parse of one fight in FG, using max 57 earth pet, with Burnout3, and Shield of Lava (from Velious robes and legs). This was a low mana use situation, I had no external buffs, just shield of magi and Transoms Phantasmal Protection<br>
<br>
Pet was a 70 hitter. Fight duration 102 seconds.<br>
Pet total melee output: 4,065 hp<br>
Average pet hit did 47 hp.<br>
DPS: 40<br>
pet was hit 18 times so damage shield did additional 450 hp. (4.5 DPS)<br>
Pet rooted mob 8 times so thats a possible 8x57 hp =456 hp. Boosting DPS to 44.5 theoretically just by pet melee and casts.<br>
Is earth pet root an &quot;all or nothing&quot; or &quot;partial&quot; resist type??<br>
<br>
Damage by me: 4125. Note using Boots to pull, and nuke through fight, finishing mob with Shock of Fiery Blades just after dimissing pet to get full xp. my engagment time 123 sec.<br>
My DPS: 33.5<br>
<br>
<br>
Total DPS: 82.5 (33.5 + 44.5 + 4.5)<br>
<br>
