<br>
Lets see:<br>
<br>
Before the recent pet change, the difference in our 49 pets and our 57+ pets for damage output where neglible. Regardless of how powerful we were at 49, we are going to have an expectation to be considerably stronger at 57. Alot do make this comparison, and have ruled it unfair, and unsatisifying. I know for me, this is my ultimate measurement for our class. <br>
<br>
Now, lets look at what melees received from 50 to 60.<br>
<br>
A. New Disciplines<br>
B. More, better, flexible caster-type items<br>
C. Skills become more significant above 50.<br>
D. AA skills that make ours look disgusting. <br>
<br>
With all these in mind, a warrior can go from someone who can't solo anything, to a class that can solo rather well. That's something to look foward to. Thats something to work for. <br>
<br>
<br>
I guess an extreme version of my point would be:<br>
<br>
If a level 4 magician had all the abilities, strength and usefulness at level as they do at level 49, would ANYONE really be satisified playing the class at 49? <br>
<br>
The problem I see is that this is a catch 22 scenario:<br>
<br>
Verant can't raise magician power too much more because in some respects we certainly are balanced. However, because of our previous overpoweredness at level 49, significant upgrades cannot occur even though we need some increase in power from 49 to make leveling to 60 worth doing.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uylaine76.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 800<br> <font color=#333333>(5/31/02 7:07:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=226.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Heh.</span><hr size=1> With epic and shield of auras you can get over 120DPS sustained over 4 hours, thats what I posted awhile back <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
